      "description": "Available for purchase is a 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine paired with a 6-speed manual transaxle. This specimen delivers 320 hp with a broad torque curve thanks to the VarioCam Plus system. The chassis dynamics are sharp, utilizing MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear suspension geometry that ensures exceptional lateral grip. Mechanically, the vehicle is robust; the IMS bearing has been retrofitted with a dual-row ceramic solution, and the cooling system\u2014including the water pump and low-temp thermostat\u2014has been recently refreshed. The braking system remains high-performance with four-piston monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina consistent with its mileage, the aerodynamic integrity and structural rigidity are uncompromised. This is a high-revving, analog enthusiast machine ready for spirited driving.",
